posts.title: Are Nike's Kobe Sneakers Ready for Prime Time? (NKE, UA)
posts.text:
Nike’s Kobe AD Cool Grey on Sale Today (NKE, UA) By Dan Moskowitz | November 22, 2016 — 11:19 AM EST 
When it comes to sneakers, NIKE, Inc. ( NKE ) is best known for its Jordan Brand. As was written in an article yesterday, consumers like to associate with champions, and with six championships—as well as the potential for more if he hadn’t temporarily switched to baseball—Michael Jordan has earned legendary status as a champion. When it comes to sneaker sales, Nike technology plays a role, but let’s be realistic. That same technology without the name “Jordan” on it wouldn’t sell nearly as well. Kobe Bryant and Steph Curry are champions, but for them, it’s not nearly as clear-cut. 
Kobe Bryant mirrored his game after Michael Jordan. That fact combined with his natural talent—and with the help of Shaq for part of his run—led him to five championship titles. This helps Nike sell shoes, but not to the extent of Jordan. It’s not as much the five titles versus six for Jordan; it’s more that Kobe just isn’t as well liked. Whether that’s fair or not is debatable, but perception plays a major role. That being the case, while the Kobe AD Cool Grey goes on sale today and offers exceptional technology, that doesn’t mean it will sell to the point of moving the revenue needle for Nike. If you’re interested in purchasing the Kobe AD Cool Grey, below are three technological features: Nike Lunarlon technology, which allows the force of impact to evenly distribute on your foot. Nike Zoom technology for thin, lightweight and durable cushioning. Nike Flywire, which strategically places filaments that function like cables on a suspension bridge to offer support precisely where it's needed. 
Nike Kobe AD Cool Grey Price: $160. 
Despite Steph Curry being more popular than Kobe these days, Under Armour, Inc.’s ( UA ) Curry 3.0 are selling for $140-$150. Prices for both the Kobe AD Cool Grey and Curry 3.0 are high, and Under Armour could run into some trouble here after the Foot Locker CEO stated that Curry 3.0 sales were off to a slow start. (See also, Curry 3.0 Could be a Slow Start for Under Armour ) 
However, the focus here is on the Kobe AD Cool Grey. If it’s selling at an even higher price point, then it might limit demand . Then again, according to Sneaker News, the Nike Kobe AD Cool Grey has a 9.0 of 10 rating. There are only 48 votes since the shoe is new, but that's a good start. Comparatively, the Curry 3.0 sports a 6.6 rating based on 168 votes. 
NKE has depreciated 22.84% over the past 12 months and currently offers a dividend yield of 1.28%. 
UA has depreciated 32.83% over the past 12 months. It does not pay a dividend. Subscribe to News To Use for the latest insights and analysis Thanks for signing up to Investopedia Insights - News to Use.

EXCLUSIVE: Queens man accused of stiffing victims at gunpoint in Facebook scheme to buy Nike sneakers, jackets NYC man stiffs victims in Facebook scheme over Nike sneakers Germaine Wright, 18, is accused of robbing two people of their Nike Air Jordan sneakers, and Nike jackets after meeting them on Facebook. (Mario Tama/Getty Images) NEW YORK DAILY NEWS   4:00 AM 
An 18-year-old Queens man ripped off two people at gunpoint after arranging on Facebook to buy coats and sneakers from them, authorities said Tuesday. 
The suspect, Germaine Wright, told police he was simply trying to get back what had been stolen from him. 
According to court papers, Wright claimed that he was robbed about a year ago and recently decided to message “different people on Facebook who looked like the people who robbed me.” 
Authorities said both crimes occurred between 12:30 a.m. and 1 a.m. on Friday.

Wright allegedly met a 29-year-old man on 90th St. in Jackson Heights and stole $26, plus the $200 Nike Air Jordan sneakers they discussed on Facebook. 
In the other incident, on 150th St. in Flushing, a 23-year-old man was robbed of two Nike jackets worth $200. 
In both cases, Wright was with 3 other men who are still at large. 
Police learned of Wright’s name from the cell phone number he gave his victims, a police source said. Wright allegedly arranged a meeting through Facebook to buy the two victims' Nike sneakers and jackets in Queens and robbed them at gunpoint. (KAREN BLEIER/AFP/Getty Images) 
Wright was charged with robbery then released without bail after his arraignment. 
He could not be reached for comment at his home in Rosedale, where a woman told the Daily News not to call anymore. 
Sources said detectives believe Wright is also responsible for another robbery on Friday in which he and a cohort stole Moncler and Canada Goose winter jackets, each of which cost last least several hundred dollars, from a 21-year-old man in Fort Greene. 
He has not yet been charged in that case.

posts.author: mary.hamilton
posts.title: Comment on LeBron James and Nike surprise high school basketball team with gear by mary.hamilton
posts.text:
Comment 
As a high school basketball coach, I’m a big fan of NBA players getting involved and doing cool things for high schools. It could be having members of the team head to a game. Or donating money for a new scoreboard or gym renovations. So, when I saw LeBron James and Nike hooked up a high school team with gear I got pretty excited. 
For those wondering, the school is Benton High School in Missouri. According to a Google search, the girls went 31-0 in 2015-16 and won the Missouri 4A state title, so they earned the reward. But it also is what makes the generous donation so cool. James really has no ties to Benton. As a native of Akron, James honestly had probably never even heard of them. Or at least we thought so. 
Instead the girls were probably getting ready for practice one day when a big box showed up. Upon opening it the girls got to see a letter from the best basketball player in the world and a whole bunch of free Nike swag. That has to be just an incredible feeling. 
Honestly, I am a bit jealous of the entire thing. Going 31-0 is special. Having LeBron James and Nike send your team things is special. Having both of them in the span of a calendar year is pretty incredible. Those girls now have two athletics stories that they can tell for the rest of their lives and be proud of. That isn’t something that most people in the world get. 
So good on James for making this happen. With just a simple conversation with Nike he has touched the lives of people he had no real reason to. That seems like a really great thing to do. 
But really we shouldn’t be that surprised. James consistently does way more than is necessary in regards to working with kids. Not only is he one of the best players in the game, he is consistently one of the best people. Related Story: Anthony Randolph finally found his place in basketball 
So congrats to the girls once again on their undefeated season and new gear. And good luck this season on keeping the winning streak going. That won’t be easy but clearly you have the talent to do this. 
Oh, and LeBron and/or anyone at Nike who may be reading this. Feel free to ship some stuff out to the teams at Dunellen High School. My contact info is in my bio if you need it. We would love it too. 
Also a big hat tip to the guys at the NBA Reddit for the find. Top Stories

posts.title: Bella Hadid Throws A Few Punches after Nike Ad Controversy
posts.text:
Chanel Adams 
Bella Hadid is showing off her athletic skills after her controversial Nike ad hit the streets of New York. The 20-year-old was seen boxing and wearing a Victoria’s Secret sports bra as part of her preparation for the upcoming Victoria’s Secret Fashion Show debut. 
Bella Hadid decided to wear just a bra while doing her workout, according to Teen Vogue . This is her first time in the annual fashion show and she wanted to show her support for the lingerie and sportswear brand by rocking a Victoria’s Secret sports bra. Hadid paired her black-and-white sports bra with a black oversized cardigan and black leggings. She also donned dark sunglasses and tied her dark tresses up into a top knot. 
She’s a knockout! Bella Hadid flashes a smile during playful boxing session ahead of Victoria Secret Fashion show -… https://t.co/9K7s6SCvP1 
— Boxing report (@Boxingreport) November 21, 2016 
Bella Hadid Wears a Victoria’s Secret Bra to Practice for the Victoria’s Secret Fashion Show https://t.co/zQTTsLoMBU 
— Nicole Vitorio (@NicoleVitorio) November 22, 2016 
Bella wore the attire as she made her way to her boxing class in New York on Monday, Nov. 21. According to the Daily Mail , Bella was seen doing an intense workout while wearing a pair of boxing gloves. She will make her debut appearance in the 2016 Victoria’s Secret Fashion Show later this month. Her sister, Gigi Hadid, is returning as well as favorites Adriana Lima, Alessandra Ambrosio, Elsa Hosk, Jasmine Tookes, and Lily Aldridge. 
The previous Victoria’s Secret Angels, Karlie Kloss, Josephine Skriver, Martha Hunt, Sara Sampaio, Stella Maxwell, and Taylor Hill will also be joining the ladies. A photo posted by Bella Hadid (@bellahadid) on Nov 16, 2016 at 6:40pm PST 
Bella Hadid’s latest sighting comes after she was slammed simply for becoming the latest face of Nike. The dark haired beauty made the announcement on Instagram, seen posing next to a gigantic billboard of herself in the center of New York City. 
“So excited to announce that I am OFFICIALLY PART OF THE @NIKE FAMILY! More coming very soon,” she wrote in her Instagram post. 
Hadid followed up with a black-and-white behind-the-scenes photo by Renella Madrano, who previously took photos of the model at her birthday party just a month ago, according to InStyle . Hadid quickly became the center of controversy when she received online criticism from those who wondered if she was a good fit for the athletic brand. A photo posted by Bella Hadid (@bellahadid) on Nov 14, 2016 at 10:15am PST A photo posted by Bella Hadid (@bellahadid) on Nov 14, 2016 at 3:40pm PST 
Fans of Nike argued that Bella’s “way too skinny to represent a sports brand” and that she “doesn’t even have an athletic body.” 
Her mother, Yolanda Hadid, fired back at her critics. The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills alum defended her daughter via TMZ . She explained that Bella used to compete in equestrian riding from when she was three years until she was diagnosed with Lyme disease at the age of 15. She had to stop riding due to the autoimmune disease that’s crippling and can affect the brain. 
“[Bella] had to give up her lifelong dream of having a professional riding career and a shot at the Olympics due to her severe symptoms and inability to ride,” Yolanda previously wrote on her Bravo blog earlier this year. “[She] struggles with symptoms of chronic Lyme every day.” A photo posted by Bella Hadid (@bellahadid) on Sep 26, 2016 at 1:00pm PDT 
Even if Bella didn’t have her athletic background, Yolanda still thinks her Nike deal is deserving.

WASHINGTON, Nov. 11, 2016 /PRNewswire/ -- U.S. Army Sgt. Matthew White with his two dogs Nike and Toffee recently received the keys to a new mortgage-free and fully-furnished Centex home in the Cherry Hill Crossing community in Dumfries, Virginia . The new home was donated by PulteGroup's Built to Honor program, which provides the gift of a new home to wounded veterans and their families across the country.
An enthusiastic group of more than 100 well-wishers, including the North Stafford HS AFJRROTC Color Guard, Combat Veteran Motorcycle Association riders, Hampton Roads 82nd Airborne Division veterans, friends, family members, PulteGroup employees, and trade partners were on hand to greet Sgt. White as he arrived to the dedication ceremony for his new home.
"It has truly been an honor to build this home for Sgt. White who served our country with honor and integrity," said Jarod Blaney, Mid-Atlantic division president of PulteGroup, which is the parent company of Centex, Pulte Homes and Del Webb. "The home is a way for us to say thank you for what Matthew has done for our country and what he has gone through on his path to recovery. We respect his bravery and dedication, fighting spirit and his giving heart, and want to join the Dumfries community in welcoming him with open arms."
During Sgt. White's second deployment to Afghanistan for Operation Enduring Freedom, he was injured on a dismounted foot patrol by an I.E.D, had countless surgeries and eventually had his right leg amputated from the knee down. In addition to competing in many running and sporting events, Matthew works with the Senate Committee on Veteran's Affairs and Board of Veteran's Appeal in the FOIA office in order to help other veterans and their families.
More than 50 national and local contractors, trade partners and PulteGroup employees donated time, money and resources to build the 1,800+ sq. ft. townhome. In particular, the home's furniture was donated by Rachael Ray from her new Rachael Ray Home collection. Sgt. White is expected to share his story of recovery and transition to civilian life on a special Veterans Day segment on the Rachael Ray Show Friday, November 11, 2016.
In advance of the event, Sgt. White also encouraged attendees to bring nonperishable food and pet supplies in support of various local community organizations. Guests as well as Pet Valu generously gave more than 100 pounds of donations and money to support Sgt. White's outreach efforts.
"I'm very involved with several anti-animal cruelty campaigns and I wanted this event to also be an opportunity to gather donations for the local shelters and rescues in the area," said Sgt. White.
Sgt. White applied for the new home through Operation FINALLY HOME, a 501(c)(3) organization that honors wounded, ill and injured veterans and widows of fallen soldiers with new custom-built, mortgage-free homes.
PulteGroup's Built to Honor™ program was launched in 2013 to recognize and thank returning military personnel who have been injured during their term of service by providing mortgage-free homes to veterans and their families. Built to Honor works in partnership with nonprofit organizations, such as Operation FINALLY HOME, to identify veteran candidates. Follow Built to Honor on Twitter: @BuiltToHonor.

posts.text: Only Nike! What Cristiano Ronaldo, Gerrard, Messi and Neymar Wore When They Made Their Professional Debut   Steven Gerrard today announced his retirement from professional football. We take a look at the boots worn by Steven Gerrard and the the three players in today's game who regularly receive signature cleats from their suppliers - Cristiano Ronaldo, Lionel Messi and Neymar - inlcuding some surprises (Gerrard received one signature boot from Adidas for his last match at Anfield). Steven Gerrard - Nike Tiempo Premier 5 Steven Gerrard, who been wearing Adidas Predator boots for almost his entire career, made his professional debut for Liverpool wearing boots not from the Three Stripes but from the Swoosh - the back, white and blue Nike Tiempo Premier soccer cleat, released for the 1998 World Cup. However, Steven Gerrard should score his first goal wearing Adidas Predator boots one month later, and remained true to Adidas until the end of his career (He wore the Predator for more than 15 years before Adidas discontinued the boot silo in 2014; Steven Gerrard switched to the Ace). Steven Gerrard scored his first goal for Liverpool as professional wearing Adidas Predator boots in 1998 Cristiano Ronaldo - Nike Mercurial Vapor After impressive performances at youth level with Portugal, Cristiano Ronaldo made his professional debut aged 17 for Sporting wearing the Nike Mercurial Vapor. He never laced up in another silo since then, which is a big exception, to say at least. Lionel Messi - Nike Air Zoom Total 90 III Lionel Messi made his Barcelona debut exactly 12 years ago, wearing Nike's Total 90 cleat. 17-year-old Leo Messi made his first La Liga appearance for Barcelona in 2004 wearing the Chrome, Black and Red Nike Air Zoom Total 90 III boots. Messi's La Liga debut came two years before he agreed a sponsorship deal with Adidas, and 11 years before he received his own signature silo. Messi had signed with Nike at the age of 14 after his move from Newell's Old Boys to Barcelona. After breaking into the first team Messi also made a number of matches in the Tiempo Legend and Mercurial Vapor II before switching to the Adidas +f50.6 TUNIT in March 2006 as he signed a reported £2million five-year deal with Adidas. Neymar - Nike Mercurial Vapor III Neymar has been wearing no other boot than the Nike Mercurial Vapor for Santos. Neymar made his professional debut in 2009 wearing a pair of Nike Mercurial Vapor football boots at the age of 17. And while the Brazilian superstar since then has become the face of the all-new Nike Hypervenom, he still wears a version that is more a Mercurial than a Hypervenom (Read more about Neymar's camouflaged boots ). Earlier this year, Nike treated Italian sneakerheads to a special reissue of the OG Nike Air Max 97 .
Featuring tricolore Italiano detailing, the drop was limited to select Italian shops, but we had a feeling that wouldn’t be the last Air Max 97 sighting of the year. Now, Nike confirmed our suspicions by declaring a wider release of the 97 in a “La Silver” colorway, just in time for the silhouette’s 20th anniversary.
To complement the announcement, several big names in the Italian fashion community shared their first impressions of the shoe with Nike.
“I have to admit that I first found them horrendous. But that kind of fascinating horrendous: brutto-bello. Freaks. Their aesthetic was totally outside of our visual vocabulary. At the time sneakers were worn very infrequently in fashion.”
Michela Gattermayer, Editor-in-Chief, ELLE (1989-2004) “As a graffiti writer it was cool because you could get a photo taken of yourself with a flash in front of a piece in a tunnel and you’d be all covered up but there was a crazy glare coming from your shoes. They made you feel like you were doing some space age stuff when you went out at night.”
Sha Ribeiro, Photographer “I can remember that you had kids turning up wearing AM97s for both the hip-hop and the hardcore nights. As an observer from the decks I thought that the AM97s were much better suited to the hardcore scene where everybody had a very clean look, was very aerodynamic, with their shaved heads and 180 + BPM music and their whole cult of synthetic velocity.”
Riccardo Balli, DJ The sneaker will see a Western European release on December 14.

posts.title: SOTW: Add Nike’s Flyknit Runner to Your Wardrobe’s Winning Streak
posts.text:
Visit the original post to see all 11 images from this gallery. 
With so many kicks on the market, finding the best of the best calls for a little bit more than just strolling into the shoe store with some spare change. To help you isolate the best of the bunch, our Sneaker of the Week is a chance for us to highlight some shoes that you need to add to your rotation. Thanks to some help from our partner Finish Line , we’re calling out the best sneakers on shelves today. 
Nike’s not afraid to innovate—taking a look at the brand’s technological advancements is nothing short of impressive. In the past four years, the revolutionary Flyknit process has become one of the brand’s most influential uppers, adorning plenty of sneakers bearing the Swoosh. Technological sport advancements aside, Nike’s been able to harness its unique textile to create shoes that are simply more exciting to see as they sprint by on the sidewalk. While several shoes in Nike’s roster have Flyknit embedded within their design, the Zoom Flyknit you see here is one of the standout continuations of a sport-meets-style lineage.
The benefits of Flyknit have certainly been expounded upon in the past, and rest assured that the Zoom Flyknit 6 is no different in that regard. Breathable as it is light, the Flyknit upper stabilized by Flywire lacing ensures a practically-weightless shoe (especially compared with other trainers). The knit may feel like a knit sock, but it still packs a significant punch. Speaking of packing a punch, it’s near impossible to miss such a vibrant Flyknit (which, according to Nike, is “micro-engineered”). It’s that technology detail that allows the upper to seamlessly gradate between a variety of colors—from royal blue, to volt green, to a turquoise toebox—while still maintaining the tactile texture that you’d expect from a knit.
While running shoes are almost a dime-a-dozen as of late, it’s refreshing to see such an expressive option from the team behind the swoosh. While lacing these up is certainly a fashion statement, you’ll be better off keeping the rest of your ‘fit a little more low-key. After all, you don’t want a cluttered wardrobe ensemble to distract from sneakers this fresh, right?
Whether you’re flexing your muscles during a training session, or simply trying to flex on your friends, the Zoom Flyknit Streak is certainly one to add to your rotation. Naturally the Phylon foam midsole and Zoom Air unit ensure that every stride feels responsive, but it also ensures that you’ll be reaching for these kicks wear after wear. With a streamlined bottom that recalls the sculpted sole found on the Nike Racer, the Zoom Flyknit Streak is just as sleek as its Nike Racing counterparts.
It’s hard not to fall for Flyknit when you see it on one of Nike’s sneakers. It’s cutting edge design isn’t just aesthetically pleasing, it also helps to literally shape a lighter, more breathable shoe. Sure, the Zoom Flyknit Streak is one that’s designed around running races, but when it comes to the stack of style points with this sneaker, you don’t want to get left in the dust.

Nike is a shoe company that was founded in 1964 as Blue Ribbon Sports, before changing to its current brand – named for the ancient Greek goddess that personified victory or triumph – in 1971 . 
Marty McFly wore white Nike sneakers with a red "swoosh" symbol on them in 1985 , and usually wore them until he could change to shoes that were appropriate for the time period. Doc Brown wore a pair of brown Nikes while at Twin Pines Mall on October 26 , 1985 . 
Since Nike shoes did not exist in 1955 , and would not be marketed until 1971, Marty wore a pair of Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star sneakers while in that time period. In 1885 , however, Marty ended up wearing his Nikes after throwing his cowboy boots away in order to distract a bear , causing Buford's gang to notice what they thought was strange writing on them — during which Stubble was heard to pronounce the name as "Nee-kay".

The brand name is barely visible at 16:34 on the DVD , as Doc speaks about fresh batteries for the walkie-talkies prior to Marty's departure from 1955. Marty's jeans cover the top of the shoes as he walks down the train tracks. posts.text:
We’re Still Hoping For A Nike ‘La Silver’ Air Max 97 Stateside Return Fashion Ashley Monaé @chicmonae   4:30   CREDIT: Nike 
For those still sick over the fact that Nike gifted Italy-based sneakerheads to an exclusive reissue of the OG Air Max 97 on Dec. 2, don’t fret. As many of us suspected, that won’t be the last sighting of the silhouette this year. 
Nike recently announced a wider release of the 97 in a “La Silver” colorway to celebrate the sneaker’s 20th anniversary. And staying true to it’s iconic look, the upper still shines in metallic hues of silver and grey along with a red Swoosh and black tongue and heel tabs. READ: Nike Confirms Release Date And Price For Nike Hyper Adapt 1.0 
In collaboration with the big news, a number of big names in the Italian fashion community shared their first impressions of the shoe with Nike. DJ Riccardo Balli spoke on how the silhouette appealed to the masses, saying, “I can remember that you had kids turning up wearing AM97s for both the hip-hop and the hardcore nights.”“As an observer from the decks I thought that the AM97s were much better suited to the hardcore scene where everybody had a very clean look, was very aerodynamic, with their shaved heads and 180 + BPM music and their whole cult of synthetic velocity,” he continued. 
“La Silver” will have its Western Europe release on Dec. 14. While there’s no word on a stateside release, we’ve got our fingers crossed that we too will have the chance to cop these kicks.

Trades from $ 3 
The Dow enjoyed another week of substantial gains following optimism about Donald Trump’s policy proposals. Meanwhile, economic data released over most of the week was encouraging. Oil prices moved higher following speculation that OPEC’s member countries and Russia were close to reaching an agreement on curtailing crude output. Additionally, prospects of the Fed hiking rates in December continued to improve. 
Last Week’s Performance 
The Dow decreased 0.2% last Friday after rising rate hike possibilities boosted the dollar to its best settlement in 13 years. Rate hike chances gained momentum following expectations that the Trump Presidency will adopt new policies including expansionary infrastructure spending and tax cuts. 
Sooner than expected rate hike chances boosted the dollar. According to Fact Set, the U.S. Dollar Index (DXY) settled at its best level since April 2003. Rising dollar weighed on export-based large-cap companies and eventually on broader markets. Moreover, oil prices fell after Baker Hughes Incorporated ( BHI - Free Report ) reported that U.S. oil rig counts experienced its biggest increase in 16 months. 
The index increased 0.1% over last week. Most of last week’s gains came on the back of encouraging domestic economic data and Fed Chairwoman Janet Yellen’s testimony. Yellen indicated that a rate hike after next month’s policy meeting was definitely on the table. 
The Dow This Week 
The index increased 0.5% on Monday following strong surge in oil prices and sell-off in the dollar. Oil prices jumped following speculations that major OPEC members and Russia were likely to reach a deal to curtail crude production by the end of this month. Moreover, countries like Iraq and Iran, who were previously unwilling to limit crude production, also backed the deal. 
Separately, the dollar fell yesterday primarily because the greenback became vulnerable to a sell-off after registering a rapid increase over the last ten sessions. Thin trading ahead of the Thanksgiving holiday also weighed on the greenback. 
The index increased 0.4% on Tuesday following rising expectations from Donald Trump’s policy proposals and encouraging housing data. The Dow moved past the psychological levels of 2,200. Markets moved up following continued expectations that Trump will adopt new policies, including expansionary infrastructure spending, environmental and financial deregulation and tax cuts. 
Moreover, Trump said that bilateral trade deals will be negotiated in order to “bring jobs and industry back onto American shores. Existing homes sales rose 2% in October from September to a seasonally adjusted rate of 5.60 million, to reach the highest annualized rate in more than nine years. 
The index increased 0.3% on Wednesday after strong durable orders and Donald Trump’s economic agenda boosted the industrial sector. The Dow reached a record high level for the third straight session following continued expectations that Trump will adopt new policies to improve the economy. Moreover, orders for durable goods in the U.S. registered its best increase in a year. 
Further, minutes from the Fed’s November meeting showed that following labor market improvements and higher inflation, policy makers were in agreement that interest rates should be raised "relatively soon". Markets were closed on Thursday following the Thanksgiving Day holiday. 
Components Moving the Index 
NIKE, Inc. ( NKE - Free Report ) announced a 13% hike in its quarterly cash dividend to 18 cents per share. The new dividend, applicable for Nike’s Class A and B shares, will be paid on Jan 3, 2017, to shareholders on record as of Dec 5, 2016. Notably, this represents the company’s fifteenth consecutive year of dividend hike, further underscoring its healthy cash flows and robust potential. 
Additionally, Zacks Rank #3 (Hold) rated Nike repurchased 19 million shares for $1.1 billion in the last reported quarter, under its $12 billion share repurchase program approved in Nov 2015. With this, the company had repurchased about 39 million shares for roughly $2.2 billion under the program. (Read: NIKE ( NKE - Free Report ) Hikes Dividend, Bolsters Shareholders' Confidence ) 
The Boeing Company ( BA - Free Report ) and Textron Inc.’s ( TXT - Free Report ) strategic joint venture (JV) Bell-Boeing’s – wholly owned subsidiary Bell Helicopter – recently secured a modification contract worth $267.3 million. Work related to this deal is scheduled to be over by Nov 2018. Boeing has a Zacks Rank #3. 
Per the terms of the deal, the JV will offer additional joint performance-based logistic support to the Marine Corps MV-22 and the Air Force and Special Operations Command CV-22 jets. The contract will utilize fiscal 2017 operations and maintenance funds of the U.S. Navy, Special Operations Command and Air Force as well as fiscal 2017 aircraft procurement funds of the U.S. Navy. 
The contract was awarded by the Naval Air Systems Command, Patuxent River, MD. Majority of the work will be carried out in Fort Worth, TX, Ridley Park, PA and other locations across the U.S. as well as outside the continental U.S. (Read: Bell-Boeing JV Wins $267M Navy Deal for CV-22, MV-22 Jets ) 
The Coca-Cola Company ( KO - Free Report ) entered into an agreement to divest its bottling assets in China for 5.87 billion yuan ($852 million), as part of its refranchising strategy to focus more on its core strengths of building great brands and leading a strong, global franchise system. 
The agreement has been signed between Coca-Cola and its three main bottling groups in China: Coca-Cola Bottling Investments Group China (“BIG”), COFCO Coca-Cola Beverages Limited (a subsidiary of COFCO Corporation, “COFCO”) and Swire Beverages Holdings Limited (“Swire”). 
Per the deal, COFCO, Swire will buy the entire bottling territory owned in China by Coca-Cola’s BIG. The cola giant currently owns approximately a third of its bottling in China, with the balance split roughly between Swire and China Foods Ltd., which is part of state-owned COFCO Ltd. 
Post the completion of the deal, COFCO will own and operate 18 bottling plants while Swire will own and manage 17 in Mainland China. However, the divestment agreement in China is subject to regulatory approvals. The stock has a Zacks Rank #3. You can see the complete list of today’s Zacks #1 Rank (Strong Buy) stocks here. 
IBM Corporation ( IBM - Free Report ) has announced the addition of four new cloud data centers in the U.K. that are capable of crunching huge amounts of data using their in- built cognitive intelligence technology. 
The opening of the new cloud data centers is a step forward by Zacks Rank #3 rated IBM to meet the growing demand for cloud computing in the U.K. and across the globe as well as provide innovative solutions to its clients. IBM Cloud will now have six cloud data centers in the UK, 16 cloud data centers throughout Europe and over 50 cloud data centers throughout the world. (Read: IBM Expands Cloud Datacenters in the UK to Bolster Growth ) 
Johnson & Johnson ’s ( JNJ - Free Report ) subsidiary, Janssen, announced that the FDA has approved its immunotherapy Darzalex to be used in combination with standard-of-care – Velcade (a proteasome inhibitor/PI) and dexamethasone or Revlimid (an immmunomodulatory agent) and dexamethasone – for the treatment of patients with multiple myeloma who have received at least one prior therapy. Johnson & Johnson has a Zacks Rank #3. 
The approval came three months after a supplemental Biologics License Application (sBLA) was submitted in August. The FDA had granted breakthrough therapy designation to Darzalex for the combination use in July. Regulatory application for the indication is under review in the EU. (Read: J&J Immunotherapy Darzalex OK'd for Label Expansion by FDA )

Nov. 25: Cross country roundup Friday Nov 25, 2016 at 7:50 PM Nov 25, 2016 at 7:54 PM 
Nike regionals 
The Nike New York Regional cross country race will be held at Bowdoin Park in Wappingers Falls at 9 a.m.Saturday. Section 9 team champions Mount Academy and Warwick will be participating, as will the Washingtonville boys and Warwick girls. 
The website Tully Runners has computer rated the participants and has the Warwick boys finishing eighth, the Mount 13th, Washingtonville 19th and F.D. Roosevelt 20th and the Warwick girls 10th. Warwick’s Behailu Bekele-Arcuri (the OCIAA and Class A champion) and Thomas Gardiner are rated in the top 25 in the state. 
New York Region championships 
Boys (11:30 a.m.) 
Mount Academy: Brendan Baird; Daryl Blough; Justin Compy; Jamie Keiderling; Adam King; Bernard King; Kent Kurtz. 
Warwick: Behailu Bekele-Arcuri; Thomas Gardiner; Rory Grady; Daniel Lindstrom; Jason Nafash; Thomas Nafash; Sean Quinn. 
Washingtonville: Matthew Barbookles; Paul Catalano; Thomas Garrison; Liam Gildea; Thomas Lawless; Bryan Nienstadt; Thomas Quinn. 
F.D. Roosevelt (Fireside RC): Joey Colaizzo; John Ryan Farrell; Liam Farrell; Justin Lang; Tito Maresca; Wyatt Matyas; Anthony Sava). 
Girls (12:05 p.m.) 
Warwick: Danielle Bartolotta; Michaela Calandra; Lauren Fox; Bridget Fox; Bridget Higgins; Fiona Mulvihill; Jennie Prial; Genevieve Reilly. 
Washingtonville: Brianna Lawless. 
New York open race (9 a.m.) 
Mount Academy: Darren Baird; Kent Kleinsasser; Nate Kurtz; Edwin Moody. 
Foot Locker regionals 
The Foot Locker Northeast Regional cross country race will be held Saturday at Van Cortlandt Park in the Bronx. The championship boys race goes off at 11 a.m., followed by the girls at 11:30 a.m. There are junior/senior races that follow in the noon hour, and freshman/sophomore races that precede in the 10 a.m. hour. 
Goshen senior Olivia Elston, the OCIAA and Section 9 Class B champ and state runner-up, has a good opportunity to grab one of the top 10 finishing spots, assuring herself a trip to San Diego for nationals. About Us

The Dow enjoyed another week of substantial gains following optimism about Donald Trump’s policy proposals. Meanwhile, economic data released over most of the week was encouraging. Oil prices moved higher following speculation that OPEC’s member countries and Russia were close to reaching an agreement on curtailing crude output. Additionally, prospects of the Fed hiking rates in December continued to improve.
Last Week’s Performance 
The Dow decreased 0.2% last Friday after rising rate hike possibilities boosted the dollar to its best settlement in 13 years. Rate hike chances gained momentum following expectations that the Trump Presidency will adopt new policies including expansionary infrastructure spending and tax cuts.
Sooner than expected rate hike chances boosted the dollar. According to Fact Set, the U.S. Dollar Index (DXY) settled at its best level since April 2003. Rising dollar weighed on export-based large-cap companies and eventually on broader markets. Moreover, oil prices fell after Baker Hughes Incorporated ( BHI - Free Report ) reported that U.S. oil rig counts experienced its biggest increase in 16 months.
The index increased 0.1% over last week. Most of last week’s gains came on the back of encouraging domestic economic data and Fed Chairwoman Janet Yellen’s testimony. Yellen indicated that a rate hike after next month’s policy meeting was definitely on the table.
The Dow   This   Week 
The index increased 0.5% on Monday following strong surge in oil prices and sell-off in the dollar. Oil prices jumped following speculations that major OPEC members and Russia were likely to reach a deal to curtail crude production by the end of this month. Moreover, countries like Iraq and Iran, who were previously unwilling to limit crude production, also backed the deal.
Separately, the dollar fell yesterday primarily because the greenback became vulnerable to a sell-off after registering a rapid increase over the last ten sessions. Thin trading ahead of the Thanksgiving holiday also weighed on the greenback.
The index increased 0.4% on Tuesday following rising expectations from Donald Trump’s policy proposals and encouraging housing data. The Dow moved past the psychological levels of 2,200. Markets moved up following continued expectations that Trump will adopt new policies, including expansionary infrastructure spending, environmental and financial deregulation and tax cuts.
Moreover, Trump said that bilateral trade deals will be negotiated in order to “bring jobs and industry back onto American shores. Existing homes sales rose 2% in October from September to a seasonally adjusted rate of 5.60 million, to reach the highest annualized rate in more than nine years.
The index increased 0.3% on Wednesday after strong durable orders and Donald Trump’s economic agenda boosted the industrial sector. The Dow reached a record high level for the third straight session following continued expectations that Trump will adopt new policies to improve the economy. Moreover, orders for durable goods in the U.S. registered its best increase in a year.
Further, minutes from the Fed’s November meeting showed that following labor market improvements and higher inflation, policy makers were in agreement that interest rates should be raised "relatively soon". Markets were closed on Thursday following the Thanksgiving Day holiday.
Components Moving the Index 
NIKE, Inc. ( NKE - Free Report ) announced a 13% hike in its quarterly cash dividend to 18 cents per share. The new dividend, applicable for Nike’s Class A and B shares, will be paid on Jan 3, 2017, to shareholders on record as of Dec 5, 2016. Notably, this represents the company’s fifteenth consecutive year of dividend hike, further underscoring its healthy cash flows and robust potential.
Additionally, Zacks Rank #3 (Hold) rated Nike repurchased 19 million shares for $1.1 billion in the last reported quarter, under its $12 billion share repurchase program approved in Nov 2015. With this, the company had repurchased about 39 million shares for roughly $2.2 billion under the program. (Read: NIKE ( NKE - Free Report ) Hikes Dividend, Bolsters Shareholders' Confidence )
The Boeing Company ( BA - Free Report ) and Textron Inc.’s ( TXT - Free Report ) strategic joint venture (JV) Bell-Boeing’s – wholly owned subsidiary Bell Helicopter – recently secured a modification contract worth $267.3 million. Work related to this deal is scheduled to be over by Nov 2018. Boeing has a Zacks Rank #3.
Per the terms of the deal, the JV will offer additional joint performance-based logistic support to the Marine Corps MV-22 and the Air Force and Special Operations Command CV-22 jets. The contract will utilize fiscal 2017 operations and maintenance funds of the U.S. Navy, Special Operations Command and Air Force as well as fiscal 2017 aircraft procurement funds of the U.S. Navy.
The contract was awarded by the Naval Air Systems Command, Patuxent River, MD. Majority of the work will be carried out in Fort Worth, TX, Ridley Park, PA and other locations across the U.S. as well as outside the continental U.S. (Read: Bell-Boeing JV Wins $267M Navy Deal for CV-22, MV-22 Jets )
The Coca-Cola Company ( KO - Free Report ) entered into an agreement to divest its bottling assets in China for 5.87 billion yuan ($852 million), as part of its refranchising strategy to focus more on its core strengths of building great brands and leading a strong, global franchise system.
The agreement has been signed between Coca-Cola and its three main bottling groups in China: Coca-Cola Bottling Investments Group China (“BIG”), COFCO Coca-Cola Beverages Limited (a subsidiary of COFCO Corporation, “COFCO”) and Swire Beverages Holdings Limited (“Swire”).
Per the deal, COFCO, Swire will buy the entire bottling territory owned in China by Coca-Cola’s BIG. The cola giant currently owns approximately a third of its bottling in China, with the balance split roughly between Swire and China Foods Ltd., which is part of state-owned COFCO Ltd.
Post the completion of the deal, COFCO will own and operate 18 bottling plants while Swire will own and manage 17 in Mainland China. However, the divestment agreement in China is subject to regulatory approvals. The stock has a Zacks Rank #3. You can see the complete list of today’s Zacks #1 Rank (Strong Buy) stocks here. 
IBM Corporation ( IBM - Free Report ) has announced the addition of four new cloud data centers in the U.K. that are capable of crunching huge amounts of data using their in-  built cognitive intelligence technology.
The opening of the new cloud data centers is a step forward by Zacks Rank #3 rated IBM to meet the growing demand for cloud computing in the U.K. and across the globe as well as provide innovative solutions to its clients. IBM Cloud will now have six cloud data centers in the UK, 16 cloud data centers throughout Europe and over 50 cloud data centers throughout the world. (Read: IBM Expands Cloud Datacenters in the UK to Bolster Growth )
Johnson & Johnson ’s ( JNJ - Free Report ) subsidiary, Janssen, announced that the FDA has approved its immunotherapy Darzalex to be used in combination with standard-of-care – Velcade (a proteasome inhibitor/PI) and dexamethasone or Revlimid (an immmunomodulatory agent) and dexamethasone – for the treatment of patients with multiple myeloma who have received at least one prior therapy. Johnson & Johnson has a Zacks Rank #3.
The approval came three months after a supplemental Biologics License Application (sBLA) was submitted in August. The FDA had granted breakthrough therapy designation to Darzalex for the combination use in July. Regulatory application for the indication is under review in the EU. (Read: J&J Immunotherapy Darzalex OK'd for Label Expansion by FDA )

While optimism about Donald Trump’s economic agenda remains undimmed, other factors are also boosting U.S. markets. For one, economic data released this week has been extremely encouraging. Additionally, it is increasingly likely that an agreement on crude production cuts will be announced next week.
This where the crucial GDP report and data on personal spending and consumer confidence scheduled for release next week assume greater significance. In case these reports are positive in nature stocks could scale even greater heights in the days ahead.

Nike Has a "Jacquard" Pack Coming for Ladies Inspired by marathon runner Joan Benoit Samuelson. By Amir Ismael 
In 1984, the first year the women's marathon was introduced to the Olympics, Joan Benoit Samuelson pioneered the way those to come by winning gold at t he Summer Games in Los Angeles. Now, NikeWomen's is channeling the spirit of Samuelson's win in the "Beautiful x Powerful Jacquard" Pack. The collection of four sneakers signifies the evolution of running footwear from Nike. 
Included in the pack are the Air Presto, Air Huarache Ultra, Air Max Thea Ultra, and Cortez Ultra. They all feature a multicolor "Jacquard" upper, black accents, white midsoles, and gum bottoms (with the exclusion of the Cortex Ultra). 
The Nike "Beautiful x Powerful Jacquard" Pack is scheduled to release on December 1 at 10 a.m. on Nike SNKRS . Prices are listed below. Nike Air Presto "Beautiful x Powerful Jacquard " - $140 Nike Air Huarache Ultra "Beautiful x Powerful Jacquard " - $130 Nike Air Max Thea Ultra "Beautiful x Powerful Jacquard " - $150 Nike Cortez Ultra "Beautiful x Powerful Jacquard " - $120

posts.text:
To follow-up on the recent orange box theme, the shoe box-inspired Nike SB Dunk Low series continues with this Pink Box edition. 
Essentially draped in the vibrant pink hue which was utilized for SB boxes back in 2005, the low-top sneaker’s leather composition is complemented with accents of black prominent on the Swooshes, branding on the heel tab and outsole, while pristine white graces the inner lining, laces, tongue tab and midsole unit. 
Finally, shoe box logos debossed on the heels cap off its notable details and respective theme. 
Priced at $120, you can purchase this pair at select Nike retailers worldwide now. 
Images: Titolo 
Author’s Take If it was 2006, I would’ve bought this silhouette instantly. My days of collecting Dunks are over, but, this is one of the better iterations this year. The colorway is solid as well.

Select members of the Buckeye squad will don special versions of the LeBron Solider 10 “Red Toe” that has been outfitted with a Nike speed plate, as it perfectly coordinates with the school’s signature colors. 
Check out the game now on ABC.
